race.comment: WHAT A RUSH (2) consistent filly who comes out of a strong contest. Gripped on late when dictating early to run third over 1000m at Kempsey in slick time. Gets a similar set-up and winning rider retains the ride. SO YOU SUGGEST (10) just under a month between runs when she faded late to run fifth over 1000m at Muswellbrook. Has a good record here and shown ability in town. Value chance. SAPPHIRE KISS (11) raced without luck at her two runs back. Snagged back from the draw and failed to get into the contest when eighth over 1000m at Gosford in BM68 class. Gets the right run and shapes as a worthy contender. MR TRACKSIDE (3) no match for the speedy Bremel last time out when sixth over 1000m at Wyong. Gets the required tempo and not to be underestimated.
